==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed in the 19th century from Vedic Sanksrit to apply to nomadic groups thought to have spread across Western Eurasia, speaking a [[Proto-Indo-European]] language. In Sanskrit, Ancient Persian and their ancestor languages it is derived from '''''[[Arya]]''''' meaning '''''[[noble]]'''''.

===Homophones===
* [[Arian]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A member of any of many nomadic peoples who are thought to have traveled throughout Western Eurasia spreading a [[Proto-Indo-European]] language. Some linguists and historians dispute the existence of the Aryans as a completely distinct group.
# {{tag|used by early 20th century Nazis}} A member of a mythical [[master race]] that would include Germans and other people of Nordic stock.
# {{tag|used by Neo-Nazis}} A [[Neo-Nazi]].

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# {{tag|No longer in technical use}} Of or pertaining to [[Indo-European]]s or Aryan peoples, cultures and languages.
# Pertaining to Nazi propaganda and racialist theories.
# Pertaining to Neo-Nazi movements, people etc.

